'''''Star Blazer''''' is a horizontally [[scrolling shooter]] programmed by Tony Suzuki for the [[Apple II]] and published by [[Broderbund Software]] in 1982.<ref name="giantlist">{{cite web |last1=Hague |first1=James |title=The Giant List of Classic Game Programmers |url=https://dadgum.com/giantlist/}}</ref> A version for [[Atari 8-bit computers]] was released in 1983 as '''''Sky Blazer'''''.<ref name="mania">{{cite web |title=Sky Blazer |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-sky-blazer_4703.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Star Blazer'' is a game in which the player is the Star Blazer, fighting back against the oppressive Bungeling Empire.<ref name="CGW6"/>

==Reception==
Barry Gittleman reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "The game is enjoyable for almost all gaming types. The only disappointment is the sudden ending after that terrific build-up. ''Star-Blazer'' must be seen to be truly appreciated."<ref name="CGW6">{{cite magazine |last=Gittleman |first=Barry |title=Mission 5 - Complete: Star Blazer Review |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=Septemberâ€“October 1982 |volume=1 |issue=6 |pages=11, 44}}</ref>

